.TH "bpf_prog_create_from_user" 9 "bpf_prog_create_from_user" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bpf_prog_create_from_user \- create an unattached filter from user buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bpf_prog_create_from_user
.BI "(struct bpf_prog **pfp "  ","
.BI "struct sock_fprog *fprog "  ","
.BI "bpf_aux_classic_check_t trans "  ","
.BI "bool save_orig "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pfp" 12
the unattached filter that is created
.IP "fprog" 12
the filter program
.IP "trans" 12
post-classic verifier transformation handler
.IP "save_orig" 12
save classic BPF program
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function effectively does the same as \fBbpf_prog_create\fP, only
that it builds up its insns buffer from user space provided buffer.
It also allows for passing a bpf_aux_classic_check_t handler.
